body.description: Streamline Your Kitchen Space with a Microwave Oven Rack Maximize your kitchen counter space with this versatile and functional microwave oven rack. Designed to fit above any countertop microwave up to 13 inches tall and 22 inches wide, this rack offers a convenient storage solution. Alternatively, you can place your microwave on top of the shelf and tuck your coffee pot underneath it. The mesh shelf top allows for ventilation for the microwave and provides a spot for you to keep your cookbooks, towels, potholders, and more. Two hooks are included to store your oven mitts, trivets, or utensils. Constructed from sturdy carbon steel with non-slip rubber feet, this rack is built to last. It's a perfect addition to any kitchen and makes for a thoughtful gift for college students, new apartment owners, or anyone looking to streamline their kitchen space.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great in a small kitchen
reviews.reviewText: I use this rack over a small oven and it gives me the extra storage I needed for all the utensils I use with this oven. We have a very small kitchen but with this rack I am not loosing any space. Quality is very good and it’s easy to put together. Everyone should use a rack like this if they have a small kitchen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very happy with my purchase!
reviews.reviewText: I really like this shelf. I assembled it easily (I’m a single woman, it took me approx 20 minutes). I bought it to use the empty space above the microwave. At first, I ordered a used one (listed in as "good as new” condition. As you can see from the last photo, it wasn’t exactly as described. I wondered what happened. A meteorite strike? An elephant? Run over by a truck?… Anyway, I sent it back for a refund (good luck to the next customer who decides to buy "used”).I spent the extra few dollars and bought new. It fit perfectly, with no space to spare. I put my digital scale on top as planned. I have a small kitchen, so counter space is precious. Overall, I’m very happy with my purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: VIPSA: For those of you rating this one star because "the legs are uneven" - no, they're not. You've simply put it together incorrectly & then blamed someone else for your incompetence lol.With shelves like this, it's important to LOOSELY attach ALL the pieces & make sure it sits evenly on a flat surface BEFORE you actually tighten the screws. K thx.Anyways, I bought this because I have a vintage piece of furniture I use as sorta an extra pantry, but the inner shelves were removed by the previous owner so its just a big empty space and I was stacking things awkwardly until I had a "DUH" moment and realized I could just buy a small metal shelf for the inside of it 😂Easy to put together & it feels sturdy. 👍🏻

This does exactly what it says. We have two, one with our microwave underneath and various kitchen staples above, with plenty of space so that the coffee, tea, condiments etc. don’t get heated by the microwave.
